#: ../../docs/classes/class_directionallight.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_directionallight.rst:19
msgid ""
"A directional light is a type of :ref:`Light <class_Light>` node that "
"models an infinite number of parallel rays covering the entire scene. It "
"is used for lights with strong intensity that are located far away from "
"the scene to model sunlight or moonlight. The worldspace location of the "
"DirectionalLight transform (origin) is ignored. Only the basis is used to"
" determine light direction."
msgstr ""

